Retail Sales Data Cleaning & Analysis

Data Cleaning: Removes errors, fixes missing information, and formats dates and numbers correctly.
Customer Analysis: Groups customers by age and region to see who is shopping the most.
Product Performance: Analyzes which products and brands are making the most profit.
Store Comparison: Looks at sales across different store types (like Flagship and Franchise) and compares them to operating costs.
Sales Trends: Identifies patterns in how and when people buy products.

Tools Used:

Pandas & NumPy: For cleaning and organizing the data.
Matplotlib & Seaborn: For creating simple charts and graphs.
Plotly: For interactive data visualizations.
